Hardware Wallet: Safety For Your Digital Currencies
It is very important to keep your digital currencies safe -- you need a hardware wallet.

It is not advisable to keep all of your funds in an online wallet, even at an exchange.

To keep your Bitcoin and Bitcoin Cash safe, you need to control your own private keys and secure those keys inside a device that is kept away from the internet.

This security comes inside a hardware wallet which you can easily purchase to store your crypto-currencies.

A hardware wallet is a necessary and a very important-to-have companion for your iPayYou account.

2-Factor Authentication
iPayYou requires each transaction to be authenticated twice:
  • With your iPayYou password. We require this when you log into your account.
  • With your mobile device.
For security, you must have your mobile device available in order to submit transactions. There are two options to authenticate your transactions with a mobile device:

Here are just some of the those benefits:

No intermediaries such as banks needed to send money
Near-instant world-wide payments

Getting Bitcoin into Your Account
iPayYou.io makes it super easy to get Bitcoin into your account. We have a program called Earn Bitcoin where we purchase various gift cards from you and pay you in Bitcoin. All you need to do is purchase these gift cards on Amazon.com by using your credit card or an Amazon.com gift card balance and then send them to us. If the vast majority of the cases, we pay you the same day as we receive them from you.
Paying Merchants that Don't Accept Bitcoin... Yet
Once you obtain Bitcoin, you want to start spending it. However, not everyone accepts it quite yet. For example, you can't buy anything on Amazon.com with Bitcoin today. You can't purchase a coffee at Starbucks. Or bid on an auction on eBay with Bitcoin.

With iPayYou, you can do all of the above by purchasing various merchants' gift cards and then use those gift cards. No need for a bank account or a credit card - just use Bitcoin!
What is Bitcoin?
Bitcoin is Real and is Valuable!
Think of bitcoin like a digital asset with a financial value.

You may hold $10 worth of this asset, $100 worth or $100,000 worth. Bitcoin is also very divisible -- in other words you may also be able to hold $0.0001 worth of bitcoin.
Works worldwide
Bitcoin is used worldwide. 1 bitcoin in the United States is valued the same as 1 bitcoin in Italy, 1 bitcoin in China, or 1 bitcoin in Kenya. Thus, you can make payments with bitcoin to anyone in the world - instantly. Because bitcoin is a world-wide standard, you may make payments to anyone with a bitcoin address.
May be bought and sold
You may easily purchase and sell bitcoin -- right here on iPayYou. If you make a payment to someone, they can withdraw that amount to a bank account by selling the bitcoin you just sent them. Current value of 1 bitcoin on iPayYou is: $42,948.85
Value fluctuates
Bitcoin is traded on bitcoin exchanges in similar ways to the way stocks are traded on stock exchanges. As a result, the value of bitcoin fluctuates -- it may go up or down in part based on how many people find bitcoin valuable. Because you are holding bitcoins in your iPayYou account, the USD value of your account may also change up or down.

You are currently holding: 0.00000000 bitcoins
Value of your account is USD: based on the 1 bitcoin value of $42,948.85

You may take a look at historical prices on various exchanges over the last couple of years.
Similar to gold and currencies
In some ways, bitcoin is similar to gold: there is a limited amount of bitcoin in circulation and additional bitcoins may not be printed by any government.

In other ways, bitcoin is similar to a currency: you may send it to anyone else with a bitcoin address.
Learn more about bitcoin
To learn more about bitcoin, visit the Bitcoin section on Wikipedia.

For news, discussion, and quite a bit of other useful information on bitcoin, visit our friends at Bitcoin.com.

    @coinqk address

    @coinqk address 001 [002...003...]

Paying With Bitcoin
Like cash but over the internet
Bitcoin is in many ways similar to cash. Your payee receives it almost instantly and is able to spend it right away. Unlike credit cards, your payee cannot accidentally take more than you send to them and they cannot use your account number to make additional unauthorized purchases.
Instant confirmations
One of the most confusing and frustrating questions anyone has when sending bitcoin is how much fee to add to the transaction so that the transaction does not get indefinitely "stuck" waiting for a confirmation.

Instead of making you guess, iPayYou continuously monitors the blockchain to see how much fee others are adding in order to get a fast confirmation (within a couple of blocks). It may be higher at certain times and lower at others. We will add just the right amount based on your size of transaction to ensure an optimal confirmation. No more guesswork!

iPayYou Announcement for the Blockchain Upgrade
Summary
Our first priority is to ensure that any Bitcoin funds you hold in your iPayYou account are safe.

Because of the coming Blockchain upgrade on August 1, 2017, we will temporarily suspend our services until this upgrade is complete. Our schedule of service suspension is provided below.

Any suspension of services by iPayYou is temporary for the duration of the Blockchain upgrade. We will restore all services once this upgrade is completed.
More Detail
On August 1, 2017, the Blockchain is going to undergo an upgrade to its core protocol. This upgrade is designed to result in a more scalable infrastructure, with faster transaction confirmations and lower fees.

Because the Blockchain is not controlled by a single party, there are multiple proposals being discussed for this upgrade. Some of these proposals may result in what is called a â€œforkâ€ in the Blockchain with two digital currencies created: Bitcoin (BTC) and Bitcoin Cash (BCC).

We will provide you with access to your Bitcoin (BTC) funds after the upgrade.

We do not currently plan on supporting Bitcoin Cash (BCH) because of the limited support for this new digital currency by the mining community. We will review demand for Bitcoin Cash (BCC) and will enable withdrawal of BCC provided sufficient demand. We cannot estimate when or if withdrawal of BCC will be available.

Customers who wish to transact in Bitcoin Cash (BCH) will need to withdraw all their Bitcoin funds from your iPayYou account and have these transactions confirmed on the Blockchain before the start of the fork.
Schedule

July 28, 2017 2pm Pacific Time

Because duration of settlement time for bitcoin purchase / sale takes a number of days, we are temporarily suspending all purchases and sale of bitcoin.

We are also suspending sale of non-Amazon.com gift cards from our â€œShoppingâ€ tab.

Amazon.com gift cards will still available for sale (up to the limit of our inventory). If you wish to sell Digital Currencies, purchasing an Amazon.com card may be a good option for you. You may redeem your Amazon.com gift card at any time at Amazon.com or you may wish to hold it until the Blockchain upgrade is completed. At that time, if you have not opened your card, we will be able to purchase back the gift card for bitcoin at the conversion rate at the time (25% restocking fee will apply).

July 31, 2017 5pm Pacific Time

All iPayYou bitcoin services will be temporarily suspended. You will not be able to withdraw bitcoin or use it to perform any other transactions, such as purchasing gift cards.

If you own a gift card already, you will still be able to send it to friends and they will be able to redeem it.

Customers who wish to transact in Bitcoin Cash (BCC) will need to withdraw their funds from your iPayYou account by this time.

August 2, 2017 12am Pacific Time

Our estimated date to restore all bitcoin services at iPayYou is August 2, 2017.

We will be monitoring the Blockchain upgrade and let you know of any updates by email and/or Twitter.
